  "text": "In healthy individuals, almost all of the iron in circulating blood is bound to Tf, while those in hepatocytes is bound to ferritin and isolated. [CITATION_1] Ferritin has the capacity to hold 2,000-5,000 iron ions per a molecule, and as mentioned above, the amount of ferritin protein expressed increases with elevated intracellular levels of iron by the IRP-IRE regulatory system (Fig. 1B) . [CITATION_2] Ferritin can therefore handle even high amounts of iron imported into hepatocytes.",
